==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''vannus'': emptyness or a void - ''vanitas'':vanity  through {{OF.}} ''vanité'' to Middle English.
===Noun===


'''vanity'''
# Excessive [[pride]] in or admiration of one's own appearance or achievements.
#*'''1611''' "Then I said in my heart, as it happeneth to the fool, so it happeneth even to me and why then was I more wise? Then I said in my heart that this is also '''vanity''', for there is no more rememberence of the wise than the fool forever:" ''Ecclesiastes 2:15-16.''
# A dressing table used to apply makeup, preen and coif hair. It normally is a low table simlar to a desk with drawers and one or more mirrors atop. Either a chair or bench is used to sit upon.

